h323Gatekeeper.name: h323Gatekeeper

revisions.description: The initial version of the mib.

h323Gatekeeper.description: The MIB Module supports the functions of a H323 gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperSystemTable.name: h323GatekeeperSystemTable
h323GatekeeperSystemTable.description: This table describes the system information for instances of a gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperSystemEntry.name: h323GatekeeperSystemEntry
h323GatekeeperSystemEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the system.

h323GatekeeperSystemNameAndMaker.name: h323GatekeeperSystemNameAndMaker
h323GatekeeperSystemNameAndMaker.description: This entity's name and maker name. A textual description of this entity may be appended after the maker name.

h323GatekeeperSystemContact.name: h323GatekeeperSystemContact
h323GatekeeperSystemContact.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.

h323GatekeeperSystemLocation.name: h323GatekeeperSystemLocation
h323GatekeeperSystemLocation.description: The physical location of this system. For instance, closet, terminal room and so on

h323GatekeeperSystemUptime.name: h323GatekeeperSystemUptime
h323GatekeeperSystemUptime.description: The amount of time (in hundredths of a second) since this system was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime in MIB-II because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

h323GatekeeperSystemLocalTime.name: h323GatekeeperSystemLocalTime
h323GatekeeperSystemLocalTime.description: The local date and time of day.

h323GatekeeperConfigurationTable.name: h323GatekeeperConfigurationTable
h323GatekeeperConfigurationTable.description: This table contains configuration information for instances of a gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperConfigurationEntry.name: h323GatekeeperConfigurationEntry
h323GatekeeperConfigurationEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the configuration.

h323GatekeeperConfigurationEnableNotific.name: h323GatekeeperConfigurationEnableNotifications
h323GatekeeperConfigurationEnableNotific.description: Indicates whether notifications should be generated for this entity. The default is disabled.

h323GatekeeperConfigurationRegistrationM.name: h323GatekeeperConfigurationRegistrationMode
h323GatekeeperConfigurationRegistrationM.description: Indicates whether gatekeeper allows : 1 - all endpoints to register dynamically 2 - no endpoints to register dynamically 3 - only predefined endpoints to register dynamically

h323ZoneTable.name: h323ZoneTable
h323ZoneTable.description: The table contains the local zones supported by the Gatekeeper and the remote zones which the Gatekeeper may or has interacted with.

h323ZoneEntry.name: h323ZoneEntry
h323ZoneEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the h323ZoneTable. An entry may be created administratively or by the gatekeeper during normal gatekeeper operations. Unless otherwise specified, writable objects may be changed while h323ZoneRowStatus is 'active'.

h323ZoneIndex.name: h323ZoneIndex
h323ZoneIndex.description: An unsigned integer value whose only significance is to uniquely identify the conceptual row. The value has no significance.

h323ZoneZoneName.name: h323ZoneZoneName
h323ZoneZoneName.description: The name of the zone as fully qualifed name. e.g. zone1.area1.company.com

h323ZoneRasSignalAddressTag.name: h323ZoneRasSignalAddressTag
h323ZoneRasSignalAddressTag.description: The tag identifying the underlying type of h323ZoneRasSignalAddress.

h323ZoneRasSignalAddress.name: h323ZoneRasSignalAddress
h323ZoneRasSignalAddress.description: A RAS Signal transport address of the gatekeeper supporting the zone.

h323ZoneMaxBandwidth.name: h323ZoneMaxBandwidth
h323ZoneMaxBandwidth.description: The maximum bidirectional bandwidth which a gatekeeper can allocate to all calls in the zone. If h323ZoneLocalFlag is 'false' then this object may be 0, indicating unknown. h323ZoneMaxBandwidth is the total bidirectional data flow in units of hundred bits per second (bps). A value of 10 is 1000bps.

h323ZoneAllocatedBandwidth.name: h323ZoneAllocatedBandwidth
h323ZoneAllocatedBandwidth.description: The total bidirectional bandwidth allocated by the gatekeeper to the active calls. If h323ZoneLocalFlag is 'false' then this object does not apply. The value is in units of hundred bits per second, i.e. a value of 10 is 1000 bps. This value may not exceed the value of h323ZoneMaxBandwidth.

h323ZoneIrrFrequency.name: h323ZoneIrrFrequency
h323ZoneIrrFrequency.description: The IRR time a gatekeeper returns in a ACF.

h323ZoneLocalZone.name: h323ZoneLocalZone
h323ZoneLocalZone.description: If this gatekeeper manages the zone, then this value is 'true' otherwise it is false.

h323ZoneAdmissions.name: h323ZoneAdmissions
h323ZoneAdmissions.description: The number of ACFs by the gatekeeper. If h323ZoneLocalZone is 'false' then the value of this object has no meaning.

h323ZoneAdmissionsRejected.name: h323ZoneAdmissionsRejected
h323ZoneAdmissionsRejected.description: The number of ARJ sent by the gatekeeper. If h323ZoneLocalZone is 'false' then the value of this object has no meaning.

h323ZoneRowStatus.name: h323ZoneRowStatus
h323ZoneRowStatus.description: The row status of the entry. This object is required to create or delete rows administratively. A agent implementing this object is not required to support the values 'createAndWait' and 'notInService'.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsTable.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsTable
h323GatekeeperStatisticsTable.description: This table contains statistics information for instances of a gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsEntry.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsEntry
h323GatekeeperStatisticsEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the statistics.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsTotalErrors.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsTotalErrors
h323GatekeeperStatisticsTotalErrors.description: Total number of GK errors that have occurred in the gateway since the last startup

h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorEventTi.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorEventTime
h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorEventTi.description: The date and time for the most recent error that has occurred in the gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorSeverit.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorSeverity
h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorSeverit.description: Severity for the most recent error that has occurred in the gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorProbabl.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorProbableCause
h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorProbabl.description: Probable Cause for the most recent error that has occurred in the gatekeeper. This value must be one of the given probable causes for errors on an entity. Values for probable causes for errors on a call or errors on a connection do not apply.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorAdditio.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorAdditionalText
h323GatekeeperStatisticsLastErrorAdditio.description: String Description of the most recent error that has occurred in the gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsZoneNo.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsZoneNo
h323GatekeeperStatisticsZoneNo.description: The number of h323 local zones supported by the Gatekeeper and the remote zones which the Gatekeeper may or has interacted with.

h323GatekeeperControlsCommands.name: h323GatekeeperControlsCommands
h323GatekeeperControlsCommands.description: A value that represents a command for the gateway. For the list of possible commands, please refer to MmControlsCommands

h323GatekeeperStart.name: h323GatekeeperStart
h323GatekeeperStart.description: Signifies that the gatekeeper has started. All MIB counters have gone to zero.

h323GatekeeperGoingDown.name: h323GatekeeperGoingDown
h323GatekeeperGoingDown.description: Signifies that the gatekeeper is about to go down

h323GatekeeperError.name: h323GatekeeperError
h323GatekeeperError.description: Signifies that an error has occurred in the Gatekeeper.

h323GatekeeperCompliance.name: h323GatekeeperCompliance
h323GatekeeperCompliance.description: The set of objects required for compliance.

h323GatekeeperSystemGroup.name: h323GatekeeperSystemGroup
h323GatekeeperSystemGroup.description: The set of objects a gatekeeper must support for the GK System Description.

h323GatekeeperConfigurationGroup.name: h323GatekeeperConfigurationGroup
h323GatekeeperConfigurationGroup.description: The set of objects a gatekeeper must support for the GK Configuration.

h323GatekeeperZoneGroup.name: h323GatekeeperZoneGroup
h323GatekeeperZoneGroup.description: The set of objects a gatekeeper must support for local and remote zones.

h323GatekeeperStatisticsGroup.name: h323GatekeeperStatisticsGroup
h323GatekeeperStatisticsGroup.description: The set of objects a gatekeeper must support for statistics.

h323GatekeeperControlsGroup.name: h323GatekeeperControlsGroup
h323GatekeeperControlsGroup.description: The set of objects a gatekeeper must support for controls.

h323GatekeeperNotificationsGroup.name: h323GatekeeperNotificationsGroup
h323GatekeeperNotificationsGroup.description: The set of notification a gatekeeper must support.
